## Decisions Made
- heartbeat uses state-commit verb mode (matches the reference subcommands.md procedure) and emits no native_task_sync hint — heartbeats don't change WI status, so there's nothing to mirror.
- complete atomically commits work-items.json + loop-state.json (active_candidate_set -> null) when the WI being completed is the last `done` in the set, avoiding a separate `candidate clear --reason completed` step.
- Owner mismatch on requeue is rejected only when --owner is provided AND the WI has a non-null owner — null owner means anyone can requeue.

